## Summary

Adds config-level Policy conformance checks for sandbox posture:

```jsonc
{
  "sandbox": {
    "requireMode": ["all", "non-main"],
    "allowBackends": ["docker", "openshell"],
    "docker": {
      "denyNetworks": ["host", "container:*"],
      "requireBindMode": "ro",
      "denyDockerSocketBinds": true,
      "denyUnconfinedProfiles": true
    },
    "browser": {
      "requireCdpSourceRange": true
    }
  }
}
```

This is stacked after the refreshed #85817 head and keeps the same policy-conformance contract: it checks authored OpenClaw config and reports drift through policy/doctor findings. It does not inspect live containers, host filesystem permissions, process state, or network state, and it does not add runtime enforcement.

The PR also extends `scopes.agents.<scopeName>` so sandbox posture can be scoped to explicit runtime `agentIds`. Scope names are descriptive buckets; matching uses normalized runtime ids. The same agent may be in multiple scopes when each scope governs different fields:

```jsonc
{
  "scopes": {
    "agents": {
      "release-workspace": {
        "agentIds": ["release-agent"],
        "agents": {
          "workspace": { "allowedAccess": ["none", "ro"] }
        }
      },
      "release-sandbox": {
        "agentIds": ["release-agent"],
        "sandbox": {
          "requireMode": ["all"],
          "allowBackends": ["docker"]
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Latest update also keeps `sandboxPosture` out of the initial no-rule/missing-policy evidence path so sandbox evidence remains opt-in for policy states that actually require it.

## Verification

- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 194 tests passed
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts`
- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts`
- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md`
- `git diff --check refs/remotes/fork/policy-agent-scoped-design...HEAD`

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Policy can now express sandbox posture requirements for mode, backend, Docker network, Docker bind mode, Docker socket binds, Docker unconfined profiles, sandbox browser CDP source range, and agent-scoped sandbox overlays.

Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-85572`, rebased on the refreshed #85817 stack, using disposable `OPENCLAW_HOME`, disposable `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`, and disposable `policy.jsonc` files under `/tmp`.

Exact command run after this patch for each proof case:

```bash
OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH="$proof/<case>.openclaw.json" \
  OPENCLAW_HOME="$proof/<case>-home" \
  OPENCLAW_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=1 \
  node --import tsx src/entry.ts policy check --json
```

Failing sandbox config used `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=off`, backend `docker`, Docker network `bridge`, writable bind `/data:/data:rw`, and an enabled sandbox browser without `cdpSourceRange`. The policy required sandbox mode `all|non-main`, denied Docker network `bridge`, required bind mode `ro`, denied Docker socket/unconfined profiles, and required browser CDP source range.

Failing output summary:

```json
{
  "ok": false,
  "findings": [
    {
      "checkId": "policy/sandbox-mode-unapproved",
      "ocPath": "oc://openclaw.config/agents/defaults/sandbox/mode",
      "requirement": "oc://failing.policy.jsonc/sandbox/requireMode"
    },
    {
      "checkId": "policy/sandbox-docker-network-denied",
      "ocPath": "oc://openclaw.config/agents/defaults/sandbox/docker/network",
      "requirement": "oc://failing.policy.jsonc/sandbox/docker/denyNetworks"
    },
    {
      "checkId": "policy/sandbox-docker-bind-mode-required",
      "ocPath": "oc://openclaw.config/agents/defaults/sandbox/docker/binds/#0",
      "requirement": "oc://failing.policy.jsonc/sandbox/docker/requireBindMode"
    },
    {
      "checkId": "policy/sandbox-browser-cdp-source-range-missing",
      "ocPath": "oc://openclaw.config/agents/defaults/sandbox/browser/cdpSourceRange",
      "requirement": "oc://failing.policy.jsonc/sandbox/browser/requireCdpSourceRange"
    }
  ]
}
```

Passing sandbox config used `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=all`, backend `docker`, Docker network `none`, read-only bind `/safe:/safe:ro`, and browser `cdpSourceRange=172.21.0.1/32` against the same policy. It exited 0 and returned:

```json
{
  "ok": true,
  "findings": []
}
```

Observed result after fix: the real `openclaw policy check --json` path emitted sandbox findings for a non-conforming but config-valid sandbox posture and accepted the conforming sandbox posture with no findings.

What was not tested: live Docker/browser containers were not launched because this PR intentionally checks config conformance only, not runtime sandbox behavior.

